    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix static node positioning for non-eNB node types\n\n### Summary\nThe `place_static_node()` function in the OMG mobility generator only applied user-defined fixed coordinates to eNB nodes, ignoring the `user_fixed` setting for UE and Relay nodes. This caused UE and Relay nodes to always receive random positions even when fixed coordinates were explicitly configured.\n\nThe issue occurred because the function checked both `user_fixed` and `node->type == eNB` conditions before applying fixed positioning. When users configured fixed positions for UE or Relay nodes, the function would skip the fixed positioning logic and generate random coordinates instead.\n\nThis fix removes the node type restriction, allowing any node type with `user_fixed = true` to use fixed coordinates when they are within the valid bounds.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair2/UTIL/OMG/static.c`: Modified the condition in `place_static_node()` to only check `omg_param_list[node->type].user_fixed` instead of also requiring `node->type == eNB`\n\n### Reproduction\nTo reproduce this issue:\n1. Configure a simulation scenario with static mobility model\n2. Set `user_fixed = true` for UE or Relay nodes with specific `fixed_x` and `fixed_y` values\n3. Run the simulation\n4. Observe that UE/Relay nodes are positioned randomly instead of at the specified fixed coordinates\n5. Check the OMG logs to confirm random positions were assigned despite fixed coordinates being configured\n\nThe fix ensures that when `user_fixed` is set to true for any node type, the configured fixed coordinates will be used (if within bounds) rather than being ignored.\n"
}